text.section:
A voting center established under this section shall:
provide access to a voting system that is accessible to voters with disabilities in accordance with the federal Americans with Disabilities Act and the federal Help America Vote Act;
provide for provisional voting in accordance with Subtitle 4 of this title;
satisfy the requirements of § 10-101 of this article; and
be open for voting during the days and for the hours that the county council directs in the resolution under § 9-501(c) of this subtitle.
